types/next-auth.d.ts

NEXTAUTH TYPES FILE (next-auth.d.ts)

PURPOSE:
This file does NOT run any code.
It only teaches TypeScript about custom fields added to
User, JWT, and Session.

PROBLEM:

Default NextAuth knows only:

session.user = {
  name
  email
  image
}

But my app uses:

_id
username
isVerified
isAcceptingMessages

Without this file:

session.user.username ❌
token._id ❌

TypeScript throws errors.

------------------------------------------------

declare module "next-auth"

Used to extend NextAuth's built-in types.

------------------------------------------------

interface User

Adds custom fields to the User object.

User can now have:

_id
username
isVerified
isAcceptingMessages

Used mainly inside:

jwt({ token, user })

------------------------------------------------

interface Session

Adds custom fields to:

session.user

Now I can safely use:

session.user._id
session.user.username
session.user.isVerified

------------------------------------------------

& DefaultSession["user"]

Keeps default NextAuth fields:

name
email
image

and adds my custom fields.

Result:

session.user = {
  name,
  email,
  image,
  _id,
  username,
  isVerified,
  isAcceptingMessages
}

------------------------------------------------

declare module "next-auth/jwt"

Extends JWT type.

Now token can contain:

token._id
token.username
token.isVerified
token.isAcceptingMessages

Needed because in jwt() callback I do:

token._id = user._id
token.username = user.username

------------------------------------------------

MEMORY TRICK:

This file is a TYPE DICTIONARY.

It tells TypeScript:

User can contain:
  _id
  username
  isVerified

JWT can contain:
  _id
  username
  isVerified

Session.user can contain:
  _id
  username
  isVerified

------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT:

This file DOES NOT:

❌ Store data
❌ Create JWTs
❌ Create Sessions
❌ Run in the browser

This file ONLY provides types.

Runtime (Actual Data Flow):

Database User
      ↓
jwt()
      ↓
Token
      ↓
session()
      ↓
Frontend

TypeScript Flow:

next-auth.d.ts
      ↓
Tells TS what fields exist
      ↓
No type errors
      ↓
Autocomplete works

ONE-LINE SUMMARY:

This file extends NextAuth's default TypeScript types so my custom fields (_id, username, isVerified, isAcceptingMessages) can be used on User, JWT, and Session without TypeScript errors.





