NEXTAUTH ROUTE HANDLER

PURPOSE:

Creates NextAuth API endpoints.

File usually:

app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts

------------------------------------------------

import NextAuth from "next-auth/next";

Imports NextAuth function.

Think:

NextAuth = Authentication Engine

------------------------------------------------

import { authOptions } from "./options";

Imports configuration from:

options.ts

Contains:

- Providers
- JWT callbacks
- Session callbacks
- Secret
- Pages

------------------------------------------------

const handler = NextAuth(authOptions)

Initializes NextAuth using your configuration.

Think:

NextAuth
    +
authOptions
    ↓
Authentication System Ready

------------------------------------------------

handler

Contains all NextAuth API logic.

Examples:

/api/auth/signin
/api/auth/signout
/api/auth/session
/api/auth/callback

------------------------------------------------

export { handler as GET, handler as POST }

Makes the same handler respond to:

GET requests
POST requests

Next.js App Router requires exporting HTTP methods.

------------------------------------------------

FLOW

User clicks Login
        ↓
signIn()
        ↓
Request sent to
/api/auth/signin
        ↓
handler receives request
        ↓
authorize() runs
        ↓
JWT created
        ↓
User logged in

------------------------------------------------

MEMORY TRICK

options.ts
    ↓
Rules

route.ts
    ↓
Starts NextAuth using those rules

------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT

This file DOES NOT:

❌ Verify passwords
❌ Create JWT manually
❌ Connect database

Those are handled in authOptions.

This file ONLY:

✓ Starts NextAuth
✓ Creates auth API routes
✓ Handles GET and POST requests

------------------------------------------------

ONE-LINE SUMMARY

This file initializes NextAuth with authOptions and exposes the authentication API endpoints required for login, logout, sessions, and callbacks.